document_data.mainbody:
An '''owlbear''' was a large [[magical beast|magical]] or [[fey]] [[beast]] that looked like a cross between an [[owl]] and a [[bear]]. Notoriously aggressive and ferocious, they were among the most feared predators in the wilderness.
{{quote|Once the wolves and owlbears catch your scent, they'll follow you. If you can't keep ahead of them, they'll eat you. Slowly, if it's an owlbear that catches you. They like cruel sport with their food.|[[Florin Falconhand]]}}
{{TOC limit|3}}

Ecology.Habitats:
[[File:Owlbear TotSF.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''A brutish owlbear from the Savage Frontier.'']]
In the [[North]], [[Silver Marches]], and [[Savage Frontier]], owlbears remained quite common.<ref> They inhabited the [[Southwood]], [[Ardeep Forest]],<ref><ref> [[Far Forest]],<ref><ref> [[High Forest]],<ref><ref> and [[Misty Forest]]. These Misty Forest owlbears hunted at night<ref><ref> and sometimes roamed up to the western edge of the [[High Moor]], before quickly being driven by the local predators.<ref> They were also rumored to be found in the [[Westwood]]<ref><ref> and could be encountered in the [[Dessarin Valley]],<ref> [[Delimbiyr Vale]], [[Laughing Hollow]],<ref> and [[Triboar Trail (region)|Triboar Trail region]].

Owlbears were common in the agricultural heart of [[Amn]]<ref> and in the [[Forest of Tethir]] in [[Tethyr]].<ref>

In the [[Moonshae Isles]], owlbears were found in the realm of [[Corwell]] on the island of [[Gwynneth]] in the late 1400s DR.<ref>{{Cite dragon/376/Realmslore: Sarifal|64}}

Around the [[Moonsea]], they were found in the [[Dragonspine Mountains]]. Further south, they were around the [[Dalelands]],<ref> in the [[Desertsmouth Mountains]],<ref> in the forests of [[Shadowdale]],<ref> [[Daggerdale]] in the [[Dagger Hills]],<ref><ref><ref> and [[Deepingdale]],<ref> and in the [[Arch Wood]] between [[Archendale]] and [[Tasseldale]].<ref><ref> They occasionally also hunted in [[Battledale]] around the Three Rivers.<ref><ref>

In the great forest of [[Cormanthor]], owlbears were found in the [[starwood]] area and<ref> in the [[Elvenwood]].<ref> During the time of ancient [[Netheril]], owlbears were to be found in the [[Eastern Forest]] (later the [[Border Forest]]).<ref>

Between [[Impiltur]] and [[the Vast]], they were found in the [[Gray Forest]].<ref>{{Cite dragon/424/Eye on the Realms: The Dragon that Never Died|34,36}} Further east, in [[Rashemen]], owlbears lived in the [[Ashenwood]] and [[Erech Forest]] and hunted along the shores of [[Lake Ashane]].<ref><ref><ref> In [[Aglarond]], owlbears could be found along the coast in the uplands, rather than the Yuirwood itself.<ref>

[[Chessenta]] saw the occasional owlbear from the deep forests in the late 1400s.<ref>{{Cite dungeon/178/Backdrop: Chessenta|71}}

In the south, owlbears were endemic to the [[Forest of Amtar]]<ref> and the [[Toadsquat Mountains]].<ref> In the [[Border Kingdoms]], they dwelled in the [[Duskwood]], the [[Qurth Forest]], and the ravines north of [[Bloutar]].<ref><ref><ref>{{Cite web/The Border Kingdoms/Bloutar}}<ref>{{Cite web/The Border Kingdoms/Duskwood}} Far to the south, owlbears were found on the island of [[Nimbral]].<ref>{{Cite web/Realmslore/The Realm of Nimbral, Part Four: Nimbrian Life, Coin, and Livings}}

Owlbears had also been found in notable dungeons, including the vast dungeon of [[Undermountain]], with encounters in the [[Arcane Chambers]],<ref><ref> [[Crystal Labyrinth]],<ref> and [[Wyllowwood]].<ref><ref> The entrance to the [[Haunted Halls]] of [[Eveningstar]] in [[Cormyr]] was found to be the lair of an owlbear ''circa'' [[1360 DR]].<ref> Two owlbears wandered into [[Under Elmwood]] and laired there ''circa'' [[1367 DR]].<ref>

Usage.Trade:
[[File:Owlbear Cub CLB.jpg|thumb|250px|''Remember: an owlbear is for life, not just for Midsummer.'']]
An owlbear egg could be sold for 200 to 2,000 gp and a hatchling or young owlbear could be sold for 500 to 3,000–5,000 gp in civilized places where the market existed for them.<ref>{{Cite dragon/137/Treasures of the Wilds|21}} Wizards were the main buyers, for use as guardian creatures. Owlbear eggs were among the exotic goods transported in royal-scale caravans crossing the [[Hordelands]] to [[Kara-Tur]].<ref>

An owlbear pelt would go for 5 [[gp]]{{Cite dragon/137/Treasures of the Wilds|17}}

Usage.Crafting & Medicine:
Owlbear [[leather]] was a quality material used in the crafting of armor and in reinforcing weapons. Owlbear bone was sturdy and durable; it was used in the pommels of [[Arthane longsword]]s.<ref>{{Cite web/Forging the Realms/Thaelon Morgyr's Map}}

Owlbear feathers were made for quality [[spell component]]s.<ref>

Owlbear [[musk]] was extracted from hormonal males in mating season. It was so potent that one whiff was enough to free a creature of enchantments that dazed, stunned, or dominated the mind. A typical pouch contained enough for three uses, weighed {{SI|1|lb|long=yes}}, and was valued at 500 gp. [[Centaur]]s were especially skilled in trapping these owlbears and quickly extracting the musk glands.{{Cite dungeon/211/Glitterdust|4}}

Usage.Magic:
A [[druid]] ''circa'' [[1479 DR]] with a primal aspect could adopt the semblance of an owlbear for their ''[[wild shape]]'', as they could many other creatures, though this was no true transformation.<ref> Prior to that, after the {{YearlinkName|1372}}, a druid could not ''wild shape'' into an owlbear, it being a magical beast rather than a thing of nature.<ref><ref> [[Incarnum]]-using [[totemist]]s could bind an owlbear avatar to their arms to gain their grappling power.<ref>

An owlbear could be summoned with the ''[[monster summoning IV]]'' [[spell]]<ref><ref> or ''[[summon nature's ally V]]''.<ref>{{Cite dragon/302/The Summoner's Circle|28}} One could summon an undead owlbear skeleton with [[summon undead II]].<ref><ref>

With the ''[[find minion]]'' spell, a wizard could have a loyal owlbear minion. It would not fight to the death, unless commanded or to protect its master. They would not lay eggs, but would hibernate in winter if the climate called for it. Uniquely, an owlbear minion could transform into a regular bear or giant owl once a day for a couple of hours. The wizard master grew a crest of yellow-brown hair not unlike an owlbear's.<ref>{{Cite dragon/228/Greater Familiars of Faerûn|81,82}}
